        "goal_understanding": "The goal is to navigate a grid-based level, change the player's piece attributes (shape, color, rotation) by stepping on modifier tiles to match specific goal requirements, then step onto the activated goal cell to complete it. All goals in a level must be completed to advance.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "Each move costs 1 stamina. Running out of stamina costs a life and resets stamina to max. Losing all lives ends the game. Walls block movement and are reported as 'blocked_directions' each turn. Modifier tiles: shape modifier cycles the piece's shape (0-5), color modifier cycles color (orange->blue->green->red->orange), rotation modifier rotates 90\u00b0 clockwise (0->90->180->270->0). A goal activates only when the piece's current shape, color, and rotation all match the goal's required values. Stepping onto an activated goal completes it."
